<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4926&amp;p=44918#p44918"><![CDATA[
Well there aren't all that many Gameboy games that don't use a MBC chip. When working on my Gameboy emulator I found that out pretty quick. Most games use atleast some sort of mapper to be bigger than 32K. So I'm guessing the glop top doesn't make as much sense or maybe not with mapper chips. Either way glop tops suck cause they leave us nothing pretty to look at.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Sun Mar 29, 2009 11:49 am</p><hr />
